Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.17,0:00:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.47,0:00:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.35,0:00:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Double Ranger Kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.48,0:00:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's cheating!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.99,0:00:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to fall down when you get kicked!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.49,0:00:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The evil empire plotting world domination \N won't be defeated so easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.49,0:00:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a rule on TV that you're supposed \N to lose at the end of the show!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.21,0:00:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is your world domination progressing smoothly?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.04,0:00:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.75,0:00:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't go down!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.18,0:00:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the hard part comes after \N you've conquered the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.76,0:00:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of world are you planning to create?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.06,0:00:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.85,0:01:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just wreck everything, and that'll be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.19,0:01:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're gonna wreck everything, \N that sounds a lot more fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.61,0:01:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Foget the Rainbow Rangers, I'm \N gonna join the evil empire, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.40,0:01:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.28,0:01:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, shall we head back?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.37,0:01:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.51,0:01:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.79,0:01:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget your stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.00,0:01:21.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.28,0:03:17.20,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(292,0)\pos(360,339)}Execution
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.64,0:03:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's getting warmer out...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.73,0:03:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.02,0:03:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's Rosemary?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.33,0:03:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did she catch a cold this winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.61,0:03:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.92,0:03:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was running around outside with her friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.70,0:03:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She used to get sick every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.51,0:03:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, when she was about this old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.00,0:03:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had to rush her to the doctor \N in the middle of the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.29,0:03:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You carry that album around with you all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.50,0:03:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.67,0:03:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must have gotten big by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.80,0:03:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's in her growing years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.47,0:03:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I haven't seen her lately, I wonder \N if her face has changed, also?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.64,0:03:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.60,0:03:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm confident...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.93,0:04:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that no matter how big Rosemary gets...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.69,0:04:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll be able to recognize her immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.56,0:04:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.52,0:04:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the time is right, please show these to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.67,0:04:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're newspaper clippings from the \N time I shot that young serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.53,0:04:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and copies of written reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.39,0:04:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not asking you to explain things to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.19,0:04:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not trying to make excuses, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.90,0:04:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.18,0:04:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I want her to know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.89,0:04:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.29,0:04:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When... do you think I can see her...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.96,0:04:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask her again if she ever plans \N on seeing her father or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.24,0:04:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.79,0:05:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll be waiting for her answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.33,0:05:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home at 9 o'clock every night!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.66,0:05:07.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've really gone back to the \N way you used to be, Richard...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.71,0:05:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like when you were young, and had \N just become a police officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.51,0:05:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes are the same as when we first met.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.06,0:05:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.08,0:05:32.50,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,142)\pos(355,344)}Hessen \N Offenbach
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How does that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.60,0:05:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have special deals right now if you sign up with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.88,0:05:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we've already got insurance with another company.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.95,0:05:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please reconsider our offer, Mr. Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.12,0:05:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're happy with what we have now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.16,0:05:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have enough to pay for more anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.33,0:05:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just signed up four years ago when we moved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.25,0:05:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Four years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.88,0:05:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.50,0:05:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A place called Brunthal, near Mannheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.17,0:05:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brunthal?  That's a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.45,0:05:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you born there, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.55,0:06:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I had lived there all my life before moving here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.39,0:06:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, do you have any children, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.93,0:06:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, our son is currently attending college in Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.27,0:06:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A college student!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.98,0:06:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got the perfect insurance \N for young people right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.65,0:06:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, at least hear me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.28,0:06:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.45,0:06:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your son?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.49,0:06:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was very cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.47,0:06:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.64,0:06:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.04,0:06:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.41,0:06:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I couldn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.62,0:06:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't mind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.00,0:06:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's barely called since he started \N going to school in Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.02,0:06:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how boys are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.98,0:06:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's no fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.87,0:06:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went there today, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.23,0:06:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, to Johan's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.78,0:07:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was a pretty normal family with \N nothing at all out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.03,0:07:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...what do you think, Richard?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.20,0:07:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in my police days, I would've thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.79,0:07:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...there's nothing more suspicious than \N something that seems perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.42,0:07:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.09,0:07:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm going to scope out Johan's \N background a little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.84,0:07:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.22,0:07:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be something...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.56,0:07:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the high school Johan went to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.06,0:07:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he was at the top of his class, \N with irreproachable conduct.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.11,0:08:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.64,0:08:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm confident...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.43,0:08:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that no matter how big Rosemary gets...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.93,0:08:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll be able to recognize her immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.41,0:08:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That baby's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.45,0:08:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no way he'd look like \N Johan when he's grown up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.35,0:08:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(248,0)\pos(356,393)}Brunthal Town Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.75,0:08:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, this is his birth certificate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.84,0:08:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.51,0:08:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan Wilhelm Liebert...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.13,0:08:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Born on February 9th, 1976...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.06,0:08:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was born in this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.52,0:08:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing out of the ordinary...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.23,0:08:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Herz!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.90,0:09:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do I have to tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.78,0:09:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no smoking in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.49,0:09:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on.  Don't be so stingy, \N just give me an ashtray.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.28,0:09:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.37,0:09:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place caught on fire four years ago, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.79,0:09:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember how hard a time \N we had when all the files burned up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.37,0:09:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You restored all the records, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.25,0:09:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.50,0:09:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We restored them by having everyone \N resubmit their information.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.26,0:09:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since this is a small town...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.17,0:09:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it really didn't take that much effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.20,0:09:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, thanks for coming, Dr. Gillen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.73,0:09:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, Professor Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.07,0:09:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said Dr. Tenma came to your place \N looking for a man named Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.45,0:09:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.62,0:09:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he had no proof to back up his story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.58,0:09:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, if this person...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.54,0:10:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was the "friend" who instigated the serial murders...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.75,0:10:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...committed by Peter Jürgens that I'm researching...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.93,0:10:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then the entire chain of events can be pieced together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.80,0:10:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Dr. Gillen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.93,0:10:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.77,0:10:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll seek permission for another audience \N with Jürgens immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.81,0:10:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I show him the photograph...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.85,0:10:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...depending on his reaction...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.77,0:10:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we may be able to prove Dr. Tenma's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.33,0:11:05.04,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(471,0)\pos(365,468)} Johan Wilhelm Liebert \N 02/09/1976 - 04/01/1978
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.37,0:11:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.80,0:11:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.16,0:11:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real Johan who was born in Brunthal \N died at the age of two...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.29,0:11:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.04,0:11:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Lieberts altered their dead son's documents...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.21,0:11:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...by taking advantage of the town hall's fire, \N and made it look like he was still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.43,0:11:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.34,0:11:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.10,0:11:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the person who calls himself Johna Liebert...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.93,0:11:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just... who is he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.44,0:11:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.90,0:11:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I just told you, I gave you \N Johan's photograph to Dr. Gillen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just hope we get an answer from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.84,0:11:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, would you like to have dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.74,0:11:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, actually, I should get going...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.54,0:11:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.66,0:12:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going back to work even \N after running all day?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.58,0:12:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I might be getting a phone call
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.31,0:12:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.77,0:12:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll get to see my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.59,0:12:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.59,0:12:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moving forward is what is important, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.47,0:12:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.49,0:12:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have now fully recovered!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.69,0:12:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.12,0:12:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy?  It's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.17,0:12:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rosemary...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.13,0:12:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm doing fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.05,0:12:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we'll see each other again...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.72,0:12:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can see each other... anytime...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.35,0:13:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Richard?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.70,0:13:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.77,0:13:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This boy here, Jürgens.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.27,0:13:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you recognize him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.19,0:13:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you met him before?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.45,0:13:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know him...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.58,0:13:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said your friend Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.08,0:13:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...only sent you letters, and you never \N met him face to face, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.92,0:13:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Johan knew you very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.19,0:13:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I borrow... a ballpoint pen...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.57,0:13:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I'm forbidden to give you any objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.76,0:13:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pen, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.12,0:14:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The park...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.29,0:14:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was in the park...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.04,0:14:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The day after I killed someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.46,0:14:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Let's stop this..."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.75,0:14:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Let this be the end of it..."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.94,0:14:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what went through my head \N as I went to the park...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.34,0:14:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had a lot of kids with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.76,0:14:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.68,0:14:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to start recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.47,0:14:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you start from the beginning again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.89,0:14:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You come, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.35,0:14:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You come, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.56,0:14:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You come, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.69,0:14:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You come, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.90,0:14:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You come, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.86,0:14:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You come..."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.96,0:14:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.31,0:14:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.25,0:14:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We met at Mr. Schuwald's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.67,0:15:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Johan Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.97,0:15:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I called several times, but you weren't home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.55,0:15:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I came over in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.65,0:15:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.23,0:15:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Dr. Gillen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.65,0:15:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how did it go when you showed \N Jürgens the photograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.05,0:15:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.62,0:15:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.41,0:15:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just moments ago at the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.54,0:15:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything right now due to the questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.00,0:15:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I was careless and gave him a ballpoint pen...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.38,0:15:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we've lost an important reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.46,0:15:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Professor Reichwein...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.30,0:15:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His suicide was clearly...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.34,0:15:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a reaction to Johan's photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.14,0:15:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as the questioning is finished, I'll rush right over.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.68,0:15:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.69,0:15:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll contact Richard immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.54,0:16:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Richard...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.16,0:16:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A college report...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.29,0:16:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.37,0:16:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm researching the convention established \N by the United Nations in 1989...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.50,0:16:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the "Convention on the Rights of the Child."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.42,0:16:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like a drink, Mr. Richard?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.76,0:16:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.38,0:16:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've quit drinking, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.39,0:16:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's a smart move.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.60,0:16:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you executed that boy while you were drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.60,0:16:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.29,0:16:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it was because of the alcohol...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.40,0:16:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I did something unforgiveable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.49,0:16:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to ask you something regarding that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.82,0:16:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That boy you shot and killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.83,0:16:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was Stefan Joos, seventeen years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.83,0:16:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of crime did he commit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.17,0:16:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.00,0:17:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A seventeen year old boy committed crimes of the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.55,0:17:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nine cases of rape and murder, \N two attempted murder cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.63,0:17:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why you executed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.09,0:17:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't an execution!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.26,0:17:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.89,0:17:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, did you know that under Article 40 \N of the Convention on the Rights of the Child...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.39,0:17:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...under the power conferred by the convention...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.06,0:17:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...one is presumed innocent until there \N is firm proof he is guilty?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.06,0:17:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're aware of that, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.90,0:17:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've worked with the juvenile division before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.07,0:17:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.03,0:17:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about Article 37?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.03,0:17:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those under the age of eighteen who commit a crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.16,0:17:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...cannot be executed or given life sentences \N where there's no chance of release.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.58,0:17:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The majority of the convention...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.21,0:17:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...are the basic rights inherent \N to a person in this country...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.71,0:17:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...whether that person is an adult or a child!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.63,0:17:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I shot and killed him, it wasn't an execution!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.63,0:17:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a mistake due to alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.72,0:17:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I did something unforgiveable...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.72,0:17:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I even accept all the social reprisals I get, like this!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.68,0:17:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. Please take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.52,0:17:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to meet you so I could write my college report.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.44,0:18:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I put you in a bad mood, I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.44,0:18:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we go for a walk to get some fresh air?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.99,0:18:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take this bottle of whiskey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.28,0:18:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The night breeze is just going to get colder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.04,0:18:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Dr. Gillen!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.12,0:18:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't get a hold of Richard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.79,0:18:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he might be able to see his daughter, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.02,0:18:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I don't think they would be \N meeting at such a late hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.76,0:18:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, please tell him to be careful when \N you do get in touch with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.47,0:18:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on my way over there right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.64,0:18:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you familiar with Stefan Joos' personal history?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.27,0:18:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he was in some orphanage in \N East Germany when he was young...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.61,0:18:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you ought to know more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.96,0:18:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an extremely important \N point when discussing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.49,0:18:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The orphanage he was in...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.62,0:18:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a terrible place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.66,0:19:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a really good kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.12,0:19:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he was mistreated horribly at the orphanage
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.17,0:19:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And his mind was twisted while he stayed there...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.13,0:19:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Article 6 of the Convention on the Rights of the Child...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.76,0:19:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An inherent right to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.22,0:19:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guaranteed survival and development.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.51,0:19:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Article 8...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.81,0:19:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The preservation of identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.56,0:19:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Article 19...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.93,0:19:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Protection from abuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.10,0:19:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.23,0:19:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That nightmarish place didn't bother \N giving him those rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.25,0:19:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That place was Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.74,0:19:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to see your daughter soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.16,0:19:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How do you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.33,0:19:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.16,0:19:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it your daughter who called \N you at home before?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be able to see her tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.80,0:19:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to accomplish?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.85,0:20:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm writing my college report.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.06,0:20:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.68,0:20:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your purpose for being with Schuwald!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.61,0:20:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.61,0:20:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who... are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.95,0:20:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you shot the boy because you were drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.58,0:20:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer my question first!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.31,0:20:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that you were seen drinking at \N a bar after you shot him that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.64,0:20:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But something is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.82,0:20:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to my research...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.85,0:20:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...not one person saw you drinking \N before you killed the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.58,0:20:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't drunk when you \N shot the boy, were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.36,0:20:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.74,0:20:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were sober.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.47,0:20:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you were calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.95,0:21:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to execute him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.41,0:21:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so you calmly pulled the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.77,0:21:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.54,0:21:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.59,0:21:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you trying to forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.13,0:21:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you just lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.51,0:21:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you lying to others?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.80,0:21:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you lying to yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.31,0:21:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you confirm the boy's crimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you have the right to execute him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.94,0:21:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that by lying...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.61,0:21:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...your sin will go away?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.16,0:21:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a heavy sin...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.91,0:21:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can a man who has committed such a sin...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.08,0:21:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...really meet with his daughter and \N say he's turned  his life around?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.78,0:22:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.31,0:22:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.51,0:22:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gillen?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.54,0:22:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Dr. Gillen?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.04,0:22:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.67,0:22:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your patient, Richard Braun...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.38,0:22:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...has died.
